<h2 style="color:red;">1ST METHOD:SUKUMA WIKI,CABBAGE AND SPINACH FARMING </h2
<p>PROCEDURE1:CUT a can into two and using the lower part fill it with soil(<p1 style="color:red;">black cotton/loam soil</p1>)</p>
<p>PROCEDURE 2:scoop the sukuma  wiki or the spinach and transplant it in the can containing the siol</p>
<p>PROCEDURE 3: add some water in the can and not in excess</p>
<img src =" nrje5872.jpg" width="400" height="250">
<p>PROCEDURE 4:ensure regular checkups to the plant and ensure the plant is watered regulary and dont forget<br> adding some manure or fertilizer</p>
<p>PROCEDURE 5:use either <b>DAP</b> in planting and <b>CAN</b> in top dressing</p>
<footer>PROCEDURE 6:you can use either a used gunia,can,nylon paper or even a circular net</footer>
